        <body>
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="abab">
                <head type="title">[<hi rend="caps">ENTRANCE TO SCHAFFHAUSEN</hi>.]<ref type="gloss_textual" target="there_is_a_charmed_peace_that_aye_poem_glosses_textual.php#SCHAFFHAUSENTITLEGLOSS" /></head>
                <lg type="stanza" n="1">
                    <l>T<hi rend="smallcaps">HE</hi> eve was darkening, as we climbed</l> 
                    <l>The summit of the hill;<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="there_is_a_charmed_peace_that_aye_poem_glosses_contextual.php#THEALPSTHEALPSGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>And, cradled &#x02BC;mid the mountain&#x2010;pine,</l> 
                    <l>The wind was lying still.</l>
                    <l>Beneath the forests shadowy</l> 
                    <l>Long time our path wound on;</l>
                    <l>One narrow strip of starry sky</l>
                    <l>Between the dark firs shone.</l> 
                    <l>The drowsy gnats had ceased their song,</l>
                    <l>The birds upon the boughs were sleeping,</l> 
                    <l>And stealthily across our path</l> 
                    <l>The leveret<ref type="gloss_textual" target="schaffhausen_poem_glosses_textual.php#LEVERETGLOSS" /> was leaping.</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
